      "span_text": "Further, if we make the standard assumptions of additive inter-temporal preferences and a constant EIS, and we allow that agents 1 The rank of a demand system is the rank of the matrix of coefficients on income terms, or equivalently the dimension of the space spanned by Engel curves, consume both luxuries and necessities (so that within period preferences are non-homothetic) then the parameter of the CRRA utility function is pinned down completely by the shape of Engel curves and the EIS can be estimated without any variation in the intertemporal price."
